methodDoc.commentText:
Currently, this method should update a project. In contrast to the definition of the HTTP PUT method, this method updates an existing resource and doesn't replace it. This should be discussed/fixed in the future.
You can access this method via curl. An example of the command line could be as follows:
curl.exe -X "PUT" -H "Content-Type: application/xml" -d &#64;path/to/file http://localhost:8080/openinfra_backend/projects/{id}

This method deletes a project resource.
You can access this method via curl. An example of the command line could be as follows:
curl.exe -I -X "DELETE" http://localhost:8080/openinfra_backend/projects/{id}
